      "analysis": {
        "summary": "The deck is a 37-card main deck with an Eldlich core, heavy on hand traps and disruption, but lacks a clear win condition beyond Eldlich the Golden Lord. The extra deck is small and includes generic boss monsters like Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon and Number 38, but consistency is hurt by odd card counts (e.g., 5 Ash Blossom, 12 Eldlich the Conquistador) and missing key Eldlich spells/traps.",
        "strengths": [
          {
            "title": "Strong Disruption Suite",
            "description": "Multiple copies of Ash Blossom, Infinite Impermanence, Effect Veiler, and Droll & Lock Bird provide strong hand trap interruption."
